### Kanban API examples

# Replace <TOKEN> with a valid access token

### Get column metadata (ordered keys/labels)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/kanban/meta
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

### Get Kanban board (columns map)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/kanban
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

# Example response (200)
# {
#   "columns": {
#     "inbox": [ { "id":"abc","sender":"Alice","subject":"Meeting","summary":"Short summary...","gmail_url":"https://...","snoozed_until":null } ],
#     "todo": [],
#     "in_progress": [],
#     "done": [],
#     "snoozed": []
#   }
# }

### Move a card
POST http://localhost:8080/api/kanban/move
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

{
  "email_id": "<EMAIL_ID>",
  "to_status": "done"
}

### Snooze a card
POST http://localhost:8080/api/kanban/snooze
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

{
  "email_id": "<EMAIL_ID>",
  "until": "2025-12-10T15:00:00Z"
}

### Request a summary for a card
POST http://localhost:8080/api/kanban/summarize
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

{
  "email_id": "<EMAIL_ID>"
}

# Example response (200)
# { "ok": true, "summary": "Generated summary..." }
